Political Capital[b1]: Hungarian Guard increases risk in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from several points of view.
In the company's "warning on risks" is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of existing ethnic tensions between the gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They claimed that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the gypsy problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between gypsies and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially in terms of the stability and democratic development of the country".
We are reminded that from the autumn of 2006 onwards the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups of Hungary received increasing publicity and encouragement and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been formed in the country that describe themselves as "national self-defense associations".
