600,000 people failed to change their driver’s license
Six hundred thousand drivers have passed the date and for this reason did not manage to change their old driver’s license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials give them time until the end of the year to issue the new pass.
However, the Ministry does not fear that after the New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers without a valid passport will find themselves on the roads.
According to traffic, the pass has not been changed mainly by those who no longer even want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline in the change of passports, the offices of the metropolis are full of applications and interest in the new passport has increased.
The City Council calculates about 2,000 customers daily.
In the queues wait for half an hour.
In Prague, around 140,000 drivers have not yet taken out the new passport.
The issuance of a new passport lasts twenty days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the passport within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must change their passport and do not reach the end of the year, but will go on the roads without a valid passport will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police can fix the violation with a warning.
In the event of an administrative breach, the fine will amount to 2,500 crowns.
According to the above information, a person who does not go anywhere could receive a fine.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 crowns.
The Ministry appealed to the offices to introduce moderate fines of at most a thousand crowns.
According to transport ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka, the fine of a thousand crowns does not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driving licence is a document in which people can decide whether they want it or not.
It is not the identity card that every person should have valid.
People who do not want to drive should hand over the driver’s license.
Just bring it or send it by certified mail to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year, the cards issued during the years 1964 and 1993 are no longer valid.
However, drivers will have to gradually change the other types of driving licenses.
People with the document between 1994 and 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the passport issued between 2001 and 2004 expires in December 2013.
