In parallel with its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by Congress of the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim that both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to ensure the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of entities for markets to function efficiently.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the different supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow the provision of financial advisory services to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory societies (AFIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that the regulated secondary markets are added to the multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with the current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment service companies to disclose in the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all operations they perform, in order to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage by the Congressional Economic Commission, several amendments were incorporated, among which it highlights that the securitized debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated by what happened with the debt of US high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that can be performed by graduates in Economics and Business 30 years after the real decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work on behalf of others, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer acquisition services to different investment companies at the same time.
