What kind of insurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in case of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the passport, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being held responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the passport, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for this reason that both older than 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as the statistics reflect that they have a lower sinister rate due to their prudence.
In addition, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the likelihood of having some kind of impact.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That’s why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, it offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various inconveniences when hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the passport.
Although the ideal thing to be well insured is full risk insurance, there are other cheaper options.
Most cautious drivers can opt for a full-risk franchise, so they get the coverage of full-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This type of agreement would mean that the customer would pay a portion of the amount of the damage.
"The part of the amount of the damage that the customer contributes will be preset based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," says Luis Noguera, senior manager in Spain at First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is guaranteed protection against damage caused to third parties, but not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and the loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid damages as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, reducing the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate held by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on such a base rate.
“The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year, you can afford to increase the bonuses," Noguera explains.
After the age of 25, drivers find it easier to take out insurance, as the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is most advisable to contract a full risk with franchise.
"Normally, young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired in the event of an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the newcomer' has passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children it is preferable to negotiate full-risk insurance, as long as their financial situation allows it, of course.
Marriages with children are considered by the insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be one at all risk with a franchise (which can be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a greater amount of franchise,” said Luis Noguera.
For retirees, a full-risk insurance with a franchise (being this one of 150 euros), or one extended to third parties when you have a high level of bonus is recommended.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in case of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
