It's not the wooden boxes.
Who links the terms Sweden and wooden box, thinks of Ikea, but does not think of Andy Warhol.
Or is it?
Currently, the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow that weighs on Warhol’s list of works.
Most of the ninety-four "type" Bright-Boxes on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" international art put in doubt the authenticity of Brillo-Boxes of the year 1968 by Andy Warhol, the Moderna Museet museum in Stockholm carried out internal investigations and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which are also the "Brillo-Boxes", that the ex-director of the Muséo de Pontus Reguen
Prehistory is too complicated with a confused relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Bright-Boxes", painted the wooden boxes of red, blue and white, with the same sample that had cartons of "Bright" soap powder.
According to Warhol, at the 1968 exhibition of his works at the Moderna Museet were exhibited hundreds of Gloss-carton boxes. These were not made by Warhol (due to expenses), but were brought directly from the "Bright" cardboard factory.
These were not works of art, but specimens (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed the production of wooden crates in Sweden, but they were not exhibited at the Modern Museet.
Witnesses of those times now speak of nearly fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auction as originals of the "Bright Boxes" of "type Stockholm" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions, some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden almost a hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him were produced and exposed.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
By this time Warhol had already been dead for 3 years.
Lars Byström, the head of the conservators of the Moderna Museet Museum, investigated six Brillo-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First, their squeezed silvers were printed and grinded and then painted in oil with a brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the 1990 copies shows that the painting was applied with a roller without directly printing the pressed silvers. In addition, it is not about oil painting, but about acrylic paint.
"These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and must be removed from the official list of Andy Warhol's Bright-Boxes," says Lars Nittve, director of the Moderna Museet museum and adds that if the "Andy Warhol Art" Authentication Commission in New York will not come to any conclusion, the Moderna Museet's ex-copies will be categorized as these.
Already in July, the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious allegations" that they are soap dust boxes.
But from that moment on, everything remained in absolute silence.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers have surrendered who had lodged in a hotel in Manila and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Head Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president for corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter he could not answer for bloodshed.
Soldiers loyal to the government had stormed the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had been entangled in the building for a few hours.
Nearly half of them, including Trillanes, had a trial on Thursday for attempting a coup in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, so he could suddenly stand with some 30 supporters.
Evidently the military police who were to watch him had passed in his ranks and followed his uprising.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blocked the neighborhood around the Hotel Noble.
The president called an urgent meeting of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the national security adviser, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
"People are tired," Trillanes said.
"We call on people to come to our ranks."
General Danilo Lim, who previously led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said that soon the other military troops wanted to continue the march.
Major government critics called on Thursday for a major rally against the president.
For months, his government has been blamed for corruption.
In 2003, the financial district in Manila was a site that drew all the attention for the riot that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven coup attempts against the democratically elected government in the Philippines.
United Internet will be Versatel’s largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday, the company reported that the average price per share is 14.46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was a lot of speculation about the company’s absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial share in Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL (Digital Subscriber Line) market.
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after the Brendenberg bank increased its stake in the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market that means that the financial institution holds the equity for a third party partner.
United Internet already on the previous day made share with nearly 10 percent of the telecommunications company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the capital expansion measure placed 17.4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106.4 million euros.
United Internet bought 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies began negotiations on marketing cooperations for DSL-products.
“We are strengthening our collaboration,” the United Internet spokesman said.
The two companies founded a joint venture MSP, to acquire the competitor Freenet.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that at the outset, the two companies want to be satisfied with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, i.e. they make Freenet participate 18.49 percent.
This meant that both companies retained all options, especially participation in the Freenet joint stock company.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
So far, the United Internet and Drillisch holdings directly held 6.01 percent of the stake in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch would achieve the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of Vatas investment company was already agreed in August.
